<BaseLayout title="Case Study — Runa Kani">
  <article class="prose max-w-none">
    <h1>Runa Kani — Incident Reporting Flow</h1>
    <p><strong>Role:</strong> PM / Lead Dev / UI</p>
    <h2>Context</h2>
    <p>Emergency reporting app. Goal: reduce time‑to‑submission while preserving context (location, device state) and compliance.</p>
    <h2>Problem</h2>
    <p>Users abandoned when multi‑step verification slowed them down.</p>
    <h2>Process</h2>
    <p>Benchmarked flows, mapped friction points, built 3 prototypes (single‑PIN, dual‑PIN, multi‑PIN). Ran usability tests.</p>
    <h2>Execution</h2>
    <p>Adopted multi‑PIN with clearer affordances, prefilled context, async dispatch, and offline queue.</p>
    <h2>Results</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>−35% time‑to‑submission</li>
      <li>+22% completion rate</li>
      <li>Zero PII leakage incidents</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Lessons</h2>
    <p>Balance safety and speed; preload context; keep legal checks early but non‑blocking.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
